    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Address Parser\\n\",\"**NLP Project 27 of 100** — Split raw address text into structured fields using regex and NER.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import re, numpy as np, pandas as pd\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"addresses = [\\n    '123 Main Street, Suite 400, New York, NY 10001',\\n    '456 Oak Avenue, Los Angeles, CA 90001',\\n    '789 Pine Road, Apt 2B, Chicago, IL 60601',\\n    '1010 Elm Blvd, Houston, TX 77001',\\n    '2020 Cedar Lane, Unit 5, Seattle, WA 98101',\\n]\\n\\ndef parse_address(addr):\\n    result = {}\\n    # Street number\\n    m = re.match(r'(\\\\d+)\\\\s+', addr)\\n    result['number'] = m.group(1) if m else None\\n    # Unit/Suite/Apt\\n    m = re.search(r'(?:Suite|Apt|Unit)\\\\s*([\\\\w]+)', addr, re.IGNORECASE)\\n    result['unit'] = m.group(1) if m else None\\n    # State + ZIP\\n    m = re.search(r',\\\\s*([A-Z]{2})\\\\s+(\\\\d{5})', addr)\\n    result['state'] = m.group(1) if m else None\\n    result['zip'] = m.group(2) if m else None\\n    # City (before state)\\n    m = re.search(r',\\\\s*([A-Za-z\\\\s]+),\\\\s*[A-Z]{2}', addr)\\n    result['city'] = m.group(1).strip() if m else None\\n    # Street name (between number and first comma)\\n    m = re.search(r'\\\\d+\\\\s+(.+?)(?:,|$)', addr)\\n    street = m.group(1).strip() if m else None\\n    if street and result['unit']:\\n        street = re.sub(r',?\\\\s*(?:Suite|Apt|Unit)\\\\s*[\\\\w]+', '', street).strip()\\n    result['street'] = street\\n    return result\\n\\nfor addr in addresses:\\n    parsed = parse_address(addr)\\n    print(f'Input: {addr}')\\n    print(f'  → {parsed}\\\\n')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Regex effectively parses US-style addresses** with known formats.\\n\",\"- **For international addresses, use dedicated libraries** (usaddress, libpostal).\\n\",\"- **Edge cases**: PO Boxes, rural routes, and non-standard formats need special handling.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
